OL,3,CThe dad travelling 6,000 miles in
OL,4,Csearch of a life-saving donor
OL,6,FThe dad, from Bunbury in Cheshire, was
OL,7,Ftold he could extend his life with a
OL,8,Fstem cell transplant, but he has
OL,9,Fstruggled to find a genetic match
OL,10,Fbecause of his mixed heritage.
OL,12,FNow he is travelling to Macau, a small
OL,13,Fcountry off mainland China, in the
OL,14,Fhope that the community there will be
OL,15,Fhis best hope of finding a stem cell
OL,16,Fdonor.
OL,18,FPete's mix of Macanese, Irish and
OL,19,FEnglish has meant finding a
OL,20,Fgenetically compatible tissue type has
OL,21,Fbeen extremely difficult.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
